[
    {
        "content": "<p>This idea was first talked about in <a class=\"message-link\" href=\"/#narrow/channel/304902-show-and-tell/topic/roc-realworld.20initial.20exploration/near/491617435\">#show and tell &gt; roc-realworld initial exploration @ 💬</a> .  The basic idea is simple:  In Static Dispatch we allow the form of <code>subject.method(arg1, arg2, ...)</code>.  Sometimes though you'd like to use that method with the subject partially applied to a argument that has a matching signature.</p>\n<p>I am suggesting that if we can determine that  a) the type of <code>subject</code> is a nominal type, and b) that nominal type has a method with the name <code>method</code>(and obviously the module that the type and method come from), we can desugar to a closure.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"c1\"># Subject.roc</span>\n<span class=\"n\">module</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"no\">Subject</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">method</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n\n<span class=\"no\">Subject</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{}</span>\n\n<span class=\"kp\">new</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"p\">{}</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Subject</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"p\">{}</span>\n\n<span class=\"nb\">method</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Subject</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Str</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">U64</span>\n<span class=\"nb\">method</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"p\">{},</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">str</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\"># Implementation not important here</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"c1\"># Other.roc</span>\n<span class=\"n\">module</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[]</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Subject</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">not_important</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Result</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"no\">Str</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">U64</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">_</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"n\">subject</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Subject</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">({})</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"n\">some_effect!</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">map</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">subject</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">method</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>The <code>not_important</code> function in <code>Other.roc</code> would be desugared to:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">not_important</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Result</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"no\">Str</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">U64</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">_</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"n\">subject</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Subject</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">({})</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"n\">some_effect!</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">map</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">str</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">subject</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">method</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">str</span><span class=\"p\">))</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>which would then be desugared by SD to</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">not_important</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Result</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"no\">Str</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">U64</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">_</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">subject</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Subject</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">({})</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"n\">some_effect!</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">map</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">str</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Subject</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">method</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">subject</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">str</span><span class=\"p\">))</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 491621826,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1735829740
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Can you give an example in this thread of where you'd want to use this?</p>",
        "id": 491623331,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1735830479
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I have to run off to work, but if you watch Richard's new video in <a class=\"stream-topic\" data-stream-id=\"304902\" href=\"/#narrow/channel/304902-show-and-tell/topic/roc-realworld.20initial.20exploration\">#show and tell &gt; roc-realworld initial exploration</a>  he talks about it</p>",
        "id": 491623442,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1735830527
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I know it's for <code>Ok(router.handle_req!)</code>, but I don't know why I want this feature without reading that other thread</p>",
        "id": 491623451,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1735830529
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Though it's early</p>",
        "id": 491623457,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1735830532
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ah, ok.  Basically you want it for using a limited form of partial application in a closure position without writing out the closure</p>",
        "id": 491623561,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1735830584
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It's <strong>pure sugar</strong></p>",
        "id": 491623659,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1735830620
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And, I think people who come to the language because of PNC and SD will find that very intuitive to write as they use it a lot</p>",
        "id": 491623766,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1735830679
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>what happens if I have a custom record defined in the same module as a function named <code>foo</code> and then later I add an exposed field to the record named <code>foo</code>? Do all the usage sites silently change to being field access because that takes priority?</p>",
        "id": 491624097,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1735830840
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Note: <code>let subject = Subject</code> -&gt; <code>subject = Subject.new()</code></p>",
        "id": 491627978,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1735832595
    },
    {
        "content": "<blockquote>\n<p>Do all the usage sites silently change to being field access because that takes priority?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>At least if that happened it would immediately fail to compile</p>",
        "id": 491628122,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1735832664
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Hmm... unless the record field loaded happens to be a lambda of the exact same type as the original code</p>",
        "id": 491628175,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1735832698
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yeah</p>",
        "id": 491629398,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1735833281
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>arguably it's a bad enough idea to have a method and field of the same name that we could emit a compiler warning if you do that</p>",
        "id": 491629438,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1735833308
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>just be like \"hey this is error-prone, pick a different name for one of them\"</p>",
        "id": 491629451,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1735833316
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I can't think of a situation where it would definitely be a good idea haha</p>",
        "id": 491629477,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1735833330
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In expression contexts, I don't think <code>record.(field!)</code> is currently used for anything. Wouldn't that let us do <code>Ok(router.(handle_req!))</code> in a way reminiscent of the <code>.pass_to(...)</code> alternative?</p>",
        "id": 491629731,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1735833461
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>that's interesting <span aria-label=\"thinking\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f914\" role=\"img\" title=\"thinking\">:thinking:</span></p>",
        "id": 491630466,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1735833794
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>certainly the syntax is open right now</p>",
        "id": 491630480,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1735833802
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm not a fan of that at all. Adds weirdness and friction where it doesn't seem needed</p>",
        "id": 491633565,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1735835348
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Also, I still really hope we use <code>.(func)(args)</code> instead of <code>.pass_to(func, args)</code></p>",
        "id": 491633828,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1735835477
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So really don't want to steal the syntax currently</p>",
        "id": 491633858,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1735835493
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That's what this pushes for</p>",
        "id": 491633915,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1735835515
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Well, it's different, I suppose</p>",
        "id": 491633997,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1735835533
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah, those would be totally different meanings</p>",
        "id": 491634129,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1735835592
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"343810\">Brendan Hansknecht</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/304641-ideas/topic/Static.20Dispatch.20and.20method.20tear-offs/near/491627978\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Note: <code>let subject = Subject</code> -&gt; <code>subject = Subject.new()</code></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I've been writing too much Rust :-)</p>",
        "id": 491634276,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1735835649
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think Sam is on to something actually....</p>",
        "id": 491634527,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1735835775
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The desugaring is the same (at least textually)</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>Ok(router.(handle_req!))\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>to</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>Ok(|req| router.(handle_req!)(req))\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 491634728,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1735835828
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh no, it would have to be</p>",
        "id": 491634794,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1735835851
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"no\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">((</span><span class=\"n\">router</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">handle_req!</span><span class=\"p\">))</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>that desugars to</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"no\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">req</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">router</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">handle_req!</span><span class=\"p\">)(</span><span class=\"n\">req</span><span class=\"p\">))</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 491634915,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1735835895
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah, it is definitely different. One is using static dispatch, the other is using an imported method.</p>",
        "id": 491634998,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1735835936
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">subject</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">method</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\"># static dispatch</span>\n<span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">subject</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">method</span><span class=\"p\">)()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\"># record closure field apply</span>\n<span class=\"n\">subject</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">func</span><span class=\"p\">)()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\"># pass to local function</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 491635227,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1735836040
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"no\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">subject</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">method</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\"># static dispatch</span>\n<span class=\"no\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">((</span><span class=\"n\">subject</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">method</span><span class=\"p\">))</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\"># record closure field apply</span>\n<span class=\"no\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">subject</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">func</span><span class=\"p\">))</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\"># pass to local function - which is actual generic partial application</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 491635340,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1735836106
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"dizzy\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f635\" role=\"img\" title=\"dizzy\">:dizzy:</span></p>",
        "id": 491635470,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1735836156
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Looks logical</p>",
        "id": 491635542,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1735836192
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>in general, <code>(a)</code> evaluates to <code>a</code></p>",
        "id": 491635584,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1735836214
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I don't think we can make <code>(subject.method)</code> evaluate to something different than <code>subject.method</code></p>",
        "id": 491635607,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1735836227
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I definitely like the first half:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">subject</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">method</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\"># static dispatch</span>\n<span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">subject</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">method</span><span class=\"p\">)()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\"># record closure field apply</span>\n<span class=\"n\">subject</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">func</span><span class=\"p\">)()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\"># pass to local function</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 491635686,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1735836249
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I feel like I need to look more at the real world repo before I have an option on all of the partial application cases</p>",
        "id": 491635813,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1735836313
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Feels convenient, but not sure how necessary</p>",
        "id": 491635844,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1735836330
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Tearoffs are never necessary, but I think with method syntax it's very helpful</p>",
        "id": 491636672,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1735836645
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Sorry, necessary was the wrong word. How much I will feel the helpfulness outways the cost of adding another special cases.</p>",
        "id": 491636798,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1735836704
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>For sure</p>",
        "id": 491636824,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1735836721
    }
]